    • getCanonicalId

      public String getCanonicalId()
      Description copied from class: RestElementResource
      Returns the "canonical" id of this element, used for de-duplicating and merging included resources in cases where the same RestElementResource is loaded from multiple different inclusion paths. Generally this is going to be the RestId of the underlying entity, but it may also be some other unique identifier, such as a unique Code.
